you listening to me?

00:04:24.889 --> 00:04:26.599 position:50% align:center
[INO, NINA] Look at how
cute and little you are!

00:04:26.683 --> 00:04:29.060 position:50% align:center
I just wanna put
you in my pocket!

00:04:29.144 --> 00:04:30.478 position:50% align:center
--[HEMO] Stop it, Miss Ino!
--[HAYU] Just stop it, Inocchi!

00:04:30.562 --> 00:04:31.771 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:04:31.855 --> 00:04:33.398 position:50% align:center
Oh, uh, sorry about that.

00:04:33.481 --> 00:04:35.275 position:50% align:center
I couldn't help myself!
She looks so sweet,

00:04:35.358 --> 00:04:36.234 position:50% align:center
I had to say hi!

00:04:36.317 --> 00:04:37.652 position:50% align:center
[ROKO]
"Couldn't help yourself"?

00:04:37.736 --> 00:04:39.029 position:50% align:center
Well, if that were true,

00:04:39.112 --> 00:04:41.364 position:50% align:center
you're still not exactly
helping your case here.

00:04:41.448 --> 00:04:43.575 position:50% align:center
I see how it is.

00:04:43.658 --> 00:04:45.076 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Aw!

00:04:45.160 --> 00:04:47.120 position:50% align:center
It's a trap! Do not fall for it!

00:04:47.203 --> 00:04:50.206 position:50% align:center
[OTO] Hm, it seems like the
rumors were true after all.

00:04:50.290 --> 00:04:53.084 position:50% align:center
These girls might be a match
for our Cream Anmitsu.

00:04:53.168 --> 00:04:54.627 position:50% align:center
But not in a good way.

00:04:54.711 --> 00:04:57.005 position:50% align:center
Uh. Did you say "our"?

00:04:57.088 --> 00:05:00.216 position:50% align:center
Ah! I remember where
I recognize her from!

00:05:00.300 --> 00:05:02.886 position:50% align:center
She's the elementary-school
student who bought 300 CDs

00:05:02.969 --> 00:05:04.095 position:50% align:center
at the concert!

00:05:04.179 --> 00:05:05.555 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Seriously?

00:05:05.638 --> 00:05:07.098 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:05:07.182 --> 00:05:10.143 position:50% align:center
Uh, please don't tell me that
you're here to return them.

00:05:10.226 --> 00:05:11.853 position:50% align:center
Anything but that!

00:05:11.936 --> 00:05:13.938 position:50% align:center
[OTO] A grown woman
begging to a child?

00:05:14.022 --> 00:05:15.440 position:50% align:center
[RIRI]
Excuse me,

00:05:15.523 --> 00:05:17.650 position:50% align:center
Ms. President, how long are
you going to linger outside?

00:05:17.734 --> 00:05:18.818 position:50% align:center
What?!

00:05:20.070 --> 00:05:22.113 position:50% align:center
[HOHO] What are you
doing at Rat Productions?

00:05:22.197 --> 00:05:23.448 position:50% align:center
And why'd you
call her "President"?

00:05:23.531 --> 00:05:26.284 position:50% align:center
Oh, sorry for not
introducing you two earlier.

00:05:26.368 --> 00:05:28.078 position:50% align:center
That's the heir
of Cat Productions.

00:05:28.161 --> 00:05:29.245 position:50% align:center
She skipped a grade

00:05:29.329 --> 00:05:31.164 position:50% align:center
and graduated from
an American university.

00:05:31.247 --> 00:05:33.166 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh!

00:05:33.249 --> 00:05:35.669 position:50% align:center
And I have a business
card to prove it.

00:05:35.752 --> 00:05:38.546 position:50% align:center
[HOHO] I see it,
but I don't believe it.

00:05:38.630 --> 00:05:40.256 position:50% align:center
Even if what
you're saying's true,

00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:42.550 position:50% align:center
how's it possible for an
elementary-school student

00:05:42.634 --> 00:05:45.011 position:50% align:center
to be the acting
president of a company?

00:05:45.095 --> 00:05:48.223 position:50% align:center
No, President Oto is
actually 19-years old.

00:05:48.306 --> 00:05:50.725 position:50% align:center
What?! There's no way she's 19!

00:05:50.809 --> 00:05:52.227 position:50% align:center
[OTO]
Hmm? Why not?

00:05:52.310 --> 00:05:53.561 position:50% align:center
Are you saying I look like a kid

00:05:53.645 --> 00:05:55.522 position:50% align:center
just because I'm wearing
a school backpack?

00:05:55.605 --> 00:05:57.107 position:50% align:center
Got a problem with it?

00:05:57.190 --> 00:06:01.528 position:50% align:center
[RIRI, OTO] Cosplay's a fun
hobby for every age group!

00:06:01.611 --> 00:06:04.155 position:50% align:center
[HOHO] There's something
wrong with Cat Productions.

00:06:04.239 --> 00:06:07.283 position:50% align:center
I'm confused. Then what are you
guys doing at Rat Productions?

00:06:07.367 --> 00:06:09.035 position:50% align:center
Ah, right! What's going on?

00:06:09.119 --> 00:06:10.912 position:50% align:center
I'd be happy to
explain it to you.

00:06:10.995 --> 00:06:13.707 position:50% align:center
I'm afraid Hoho's supervisor
has made her decision,

00:06:13.790 --> 00:06:14.874 position:50% align:center
and her show's canceled.

00:06:14.958 --> 00:06:16.251 position:50% align:center
[GROUP gasps]

00:06:16.334 --> 00:06:18.169 position:50% align:center
[RIRI] But you don't
need to worry, Hoho.

00:06:18.253 --> 00:06:20.380 position:50% align:center
[RIRI] That's why the
president and I are here today.

00:06:20.463 --> 00:06:21.673 position:50% align:center
[HOHO]
Uh!

00:06:21.756 --> 00:06:23.299 position:50% align:center
If we're lucky,
maybe Miss Oto will

00:06:23.383 --> 00:06:25.635 position:50% align:center
graciously allow us
to become her servants?

00:06:25.719 --> 00:06:28.513 position:50% align:center
Hey, have a little more
self-respect, will ya?

00:06:28.596 --> 00:06:29.931 position:50% align:center
Listen up.

00:06:30.015 --> 00:06:32.392 position:50% align:center
It's true low ratings are
a big issue for your show.

00:06:32.475 --> 00:06:34.269 position:50% align:center
But the main reason
for the cancelation

00:06:34.352 --> 00:06:35.854 position:50% align:center
is that your sponsor backed out.

00:06:35.937 --> 00:06:37.439 position:50% align:center
And a late-night
program like yours

00:06:37.522 --> 00:06:40.191 position:50% align:center
just can't survive without
that financial support.

00:06:40.275 --> 00:06:41.443 position:50% align:center
But it's all going to be okay,

00:06:41.526 --> 00:06:43.528 position:50% align:center
because I've arranged
a new sponsor for you.

00:06:43.611 --> 00:06:44.529 position:50% align:center
[GROUP gasps]

00:06:44.612 --> 00:06:45.947 position:50% align:center
Y-You really did that?

00:06:46.031 --> 00:06:47.574 position:50% align:center
[OTO giggles]
You're welcome!

00:06:47.657 --> 00:06:49.534 position:50% align:center
I can pull strings to
make anything happen,

00:06:49.617 --> 00:06:50.994 position:50% align:center
since I'm a genius!

00:06:51.077 --> 00:06:55.123 position:50% align:center
Well, in that case,
go knock yourself out, Nina.

00:06:55.206 --> 00:06:56.124 position:50% align:center
What?

00:06:56.207 --> 00:06:57.834 position:50% align:center
[OTO]
What the--?

00:06:57.917 --> 00:07:00.086 position:50% align:center
Ahem. In exchange for our help,

00:07:00.170 --> 00:07:02.088 position:50% align:center
we'll need something
in return, of course.

00:07:02.172 --> 00:07:04.007 position:50% align:center
We would like Fruit Tart
to collaborate with us

00:07:04.090 --> 00:07:05.508 position:50% align:center
in an upcoming project.

00:07:05.592 --> 00:07:06.634 position:50% align:center
A new project?

00:07:06.718 --> 00:07:08.720 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh! You'll be
joining a brand new,

00:07:08.803 --> 00:07:11.514 position:50% align:center
super large-scale project
organized by Cat Productions!

00:07:11.598 --> 00:07:14.184 position:50% align:center
[GROUP] A new, super
large-scale project?

00:07:14.267 --> 00:07:15.226 position:50% align:center
[OTO]
We already have approval

00:07:15.310 --> 00:07:17.312 position:50% align:center
from Rat Productions
to move forward.

00:07:17.395 --> 00:07:20.148 position:50% align:center
And this is exactly what
your sponsor requested, too.

00:07:20.231 --> 00:07:21.900 position:50% align:center
I think the exact quote was,

00:07:21.983 --> 00:07:24.110 position:50% align:center
"Please put my precious girl
on TV more often."

00:07:24.194 --> 00:07:25.320 position:50% align:center
So that's the plan!

00:07:25.403 --> 00:07:27.072 position:50% align:center
We don't have any choice at all?

00:07:27.155 --> 00:07:28.656 position:50% align:center
[INO]
Who's the "precious girl"?

00:07:28.740 --> 00:07:31.034 position:50% align:center
How about you ask Hayu Nukui?

00:07:31.117 --> 00:07:32.243 position:50% align:center
Uh, what do you mean?

00:07:32.327 --> 00:07:34.079 position:50% align:center
You're saying the
"precious girl" is me?

00:07:34.162 --> 00:07:36.373 position:50% align:center
[INO gasps] We have a
sponsor because of you!

00:07:36.456 --> 00:07:37.999 position:50% align:center
The show won't
be canceled after all!

00:07:38.083 --> 00:07:39.334 position:50% align:center
That's amazing, Hayu!

00:07:39.417 --> 00:07:41.127 position:50% align:center
O-Okay.

00:07:41.211 --> 00:07:45.048 position:50% align:center
I'm so devoted to Fruit Tart,
I'll do anything for the group!

00:07:45.131 --> 00:07:47.050 position:50% align:center
Oh, Hayu, you're so cute!

00:07:47.133 --> 00:07:50.011 position:50% align:center
No way! I'm not going to
let you have my backpack!

00:07:50.095 --> 00:07:51.346 position:50% align:center
[OTO growls]

00:07:51.429 --> 00:07:54.599 position:50% align:center
[ROKO] Cat Productions
sure has a weird president.

00:07:54.683 --> 00:07:56.101 position:50% align:center
[RIRI]
Now that everyone's up to speed,

00:07:56.184 --> 00:07:57.769 position:50% align:center
why don't we go
meet the sponsor?

00:07:57.852 --> 00:07:59.688 position:50% align:center
[HOHO] Wait, the
sponsor's here already?

00:07:59.771 --> 00:08:01.147 position:50% align:center
Yes, of course!

00:08:01.231 --> 00:08:03.942 position:50% align:center
I thought you'd all feel
more at ease if you met the--

00:08:04.025 --> 00:08:06.152 position:50% align:center
I'll do anything for Fruit Tart!

00:08:06.236 --> 00:08:07.362 position:50% align:center
[OTO]
What are you doing?

00:08:07.445 --> 00:08:11.199 position:50% align:center
It's a perfectly normal
way to entertain VIPs.

00:08:11.282 --> 00:08:12.701 position:50% align:center
Yes, my Master.

00:08:12.784 --> 00:08:15.120 position:50% align:center
This is wrong on so many levels!

00:08:15.203 --> 00:08:16.579 position:50% align:center
Now that you mention it,

00:08:16.663 --> 00:08:19.124 position:50% align:center
I don't really know how to
"entertain" special guests.

00:08:19.207 --> 00:08:21.501 position:50% align:center
Roko, have you ever done
anything like that before?

00:08:21.584 --> 00:08:22.419 position:50% align:center
Lemme see...

00:08:22.502 --> 00:08:23.753 position:50% align:center
Hmmm.

00:08:23.837 --> 00:08:25.463 position:50% align:center
Well, I guess you
could call it that.

00:08:25.547 --> 00:08:27.882 position:50% align:center
But it was way back
when I was a little kid.

00:08:27.966 --> 00:08:29.467 position:50% align:center
Adults are so easy to please.

00:08:29.551 --> 00:08:31.553 position:50% align:center
I just used the
goody-two-shoes act.

00:08:31.636 --> 00:08:34.305 position:50% align:center
I promise I will work hard
and do my very best!

00:08:34.389 --> 00:08:36.307 position:50% align:center
What an inspiring
little girl she is!

00:08:36.391 --> 00:08:39.144 position:50% align:center
If by "inspiring" you mean
"conniving" then, you're right!

00:08:39.227 --> 00:08:40.687 position:50% align:center
So, Roko, are you saying

00:08:40.770 --> 00:08:43.189 position:50% align:center
I should also try to put
on a good girl persona?

00:08:43.273 --> 00:08:45.191 position:50% align:center
Dunno. That act
might not work for you.

00:08:45.275 --> 00:08:46.735 position:50% align:center
You're cute,
but we need to find a way

00:08:46.818 --> 00:08:48.778 position:50% align:center
to make you a little
more interesting.

00:08:48.862 --> 00:08:50.321 position:50% align:center
Based on the feedback
we've gathered,

00:08:50.405 --> 00:08:53.199 position:50% align:center
the fans seem to like the
girly side of your personality.

00:08:53.283 --> 00:08:54.951 position:50% align:center
[HOHO] So, let's try to play
that up a bit more.

00:08:55.035 --> 00:08:56.870 position:50% align:center
G-Girly?

00:08:56.953 --> 00:09:00.206 position:50% align:center
This entire time I thought I was
embodying the "cool idol" image!

00:09:00.290 --> 00:09:02.083 position:50% align:center
You know, like
the edgy rocker type.

00:09:02.167 --> 00:09:04.961 position:50% align:center
I can't take you seriously
with that outfit on.

00:09:05.045 --> 00:09:07.714 position:50% align:center
Relax, Hayu. There's no
reason for you to be scared.

00:09:07.797 --> 00:09:11.843 position:50% align:center
Yeah, it'll be fine. Your new
sponsor is very kind and gentle.

00:09:11.926 --> 00:09:14.012 position:50% align:center
You don't need to pretend
to be someone you're not.

00:09:14.095 --> 00:09:16.181 position:50% align:center
This person will accept you,
no matter what.

00:09:16.264 --> 00:09:18.767 position:50% align:center
That's right, just like
any devoted mother would.

00:09:18.850 --> 00:09:21.978 position:50% align:center
Did she say "mother"? Why do
I suddenly have a bad feeling?

00:09:22.062 --> 00:09:24.856 position:50% align:center
[gasps] The sponsor
couldn't be...

00:09:30.904 --> 00:09:32.655 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:09:32.739 --> 00:09:34.157 position:50% align:center
[RUA]
I'm Rua Nakamachi!

00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:36.201 position:50% align:center
I'm a second year in high
school, born on January first.

00:09:36.284 --> 00:09:39.996 position:50% align:center
My blood type is AB.
