00:17:52.364 --> 00:17:54.824 position:50% align:center
[INO] The first incentive
tier starts at 100 votes,

00:17:54.908 --> 00:17:56.701 position:50% align:center
then 300, 500,

00:17:56.785 --> 00:17:59.913 position:50% align:center
and then the next tier jumps
all the way up to 1,000 votes.

00:17:59.996 --> 00:18:02.415 position:50% align:center
Uh, anyone have an idea yet?

00:18:02.499 --> 00:18:03.833 position:50% align:center
Should we start
small and gradually

00:18:03.917 --> 00:18:05.877 position:50% align:center
do something bigger
for each level?

00:18:05.960 --> 00:18:07.796 position:50% align:center
It could be smart to
go big in the beginning

00:18:07.879 --> 00:18:09.506 position:50% align:center
to get people excited.

00:18:09.589 --> 00:18:13.301 position:50% align:center
[INO] Um, Miss Hoho,
all this marketing stuff...

00:18:13.385 --> 00:18:16.388 position:50% align:center
As our producer, shouldn't you
be in charge of these things?

00:18:16.471 --> 00:18:18.264 position:50% align:center
We're just a bunch of novices.

00:18:18.348 --> 00:18:23.228 position:50% align:center
Hah. You want me to lead when
I lost 100,000 yen last night?

00:18:23.311 --> 00:18:25.313 position:50% align:center
I can't stop.

00:18:25.397 --> 00:18:26.731 position:50% align:center
Go on and laugh.

00:18:26.815 --> 00:18:27.774 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Uh...

00:18:27.857 --> 00:18:30.068 position:50% align:center
O-Okay, sorry for asking.

00:18:30.151 --> 00:18:32.487 position:50% align:center
[HOHO]
If you really want my opinion,

00:18:32.570 --> 00:18:35.115 position:50% align:center
I think the perk should
feature Hayu or Nina.

00:18:35.198 --> 00:18:37.992 position:50% align:center
What?! But why would
you feature me?

00:18:38.076 --> 00:18:40.120 position:50% align:center
I can guess why you'd
want to use Nina.

00:18:40.203 --> 00:18:42.497 position:50% align:center
I mean anyone can see
the difference between us.

00:18:42.580 --> 00:18:44.124 position:50% align:center
Let's not play that game!

00:18:44.207 --> 00:18:45.625 position:50% align:center
Well, that wasn't why,

00:18:45.709 --> 00:18:48.253 position:50% align:center
or did you forget that our
secondary goal is to win back

00:18:48.336 --> 00:18:51.339 position:50% align:center
your dad's approval so your
parents can sponsor our group.

00:18:51.423 --> 00:18:53.883 position:50% align:center
I hope you'll give our sweet
daughter lots of screen time!

00:18:53.967 --> 00:18:56.011 position:50% align:center
Ah! I totally forgot about that!

00:18:56.094 --> 00:18:57.637 position:50% align:center
So, I suggest that we have Hayu

00:18:57.721 --> 00:19:01.099 position:50% align:center
say something cute like, "I love
you, Daddy" to win him over!

00:19:01.182 --> 00:19:03.560 position:50% align:center
I love you so much, Daddy.

00:19:04.728 --> 00:19:06.104 position:50% align:center
Huh.

00:19:06.187 --> 00:19:08.857 position:50% align:center
You think I'm going to do
something cheesy like that?

00:19:08.940 --> 00:19:09.899 position:50% align:center
[HAYU gasps]

00:19:09.983 --> 00:19:11.735 position:50% align:center
Are you really gonna
make me do this?

00:19:11.818 --> 00:19:13.236 position:50% align:center
[INO]
Mm-mm!

00:19:16.281 --> 00:19:19.743 position:50% align:center
I-I love you so much, Daddy.

00:19:19.826 --> 00:19:20.869 position:50% align:center
[ROKO]
Hmm.

00:19:20.952 --> 00:19:23.872 position:50% align:center
[HAYU]
I-I love you so much, Daddy.

00:19:23.955 --> 00:19:27.000 position:50% align:center
Huh. Turned out way better
than I expected it to!

00:19:27.083 --> 00:19:28.752 position:50% align:center
I'd wanna support you!

00:19:28.835 --> 00:19:31.254 position:50% align:center
[ROKO] I bet Hayu's dad
will be super touched by it!

00:19:31.338 --> 00:19:33.340 position:50% align:center
Let's use it as
one of our perks!

00:19:33.423 --> 00:19:36.509 position:50% align:center
[INO] I hope it makes all the
dads across the country happy!

00:19:36.593 --> 00:19:41.890 position:50% align:center
Why am I the only one
doing something weird?!

00:19:41.973 --> 00:19:44.642 position:50% align:center
Hi, Mommy, I love you.

00:19:44.726 --> 00:19:48.521 position:50% align:center
Hey, Big Brother,
I love you so much!

00:19:48.605 --> 00:19:52.400 position:50% align:center
[giggles] I love you
lots, Big Sister!

00:19:52.484 --> 00:19:55.779 position:50% align:center
Little Sister, little Brother,
let me give you a big hug

00:19:55.862 --> 00:19:57.864 position:50% align:center
and we can all snuggle together!

00:19:57.947 --> 00:20:01.159 position:50% align:center
Let me give you a big hug
and we can all snuggle together!

00:20:01.242 --> 00:20:02.702 position:50% align:center
[ROKO]
Okay.

00:20:02.786 --> 00:20:05.914 position:50% align:center
So now everyone has recorded
a cute video just like Hayu's.

00:20:05.997 --> 00:20:07.248 position:50% align:center
But do you actually
think that there

00:20:07.332 --> 00:20:09.292 position:50% align:center
will be a demand for
this kind of content?

00:20:09.376 --> 00:20:10.794 position:50% align:center
[GROUP sighs]

00:20:10.877 --> 00:20:12.420 position:50% align:center
Oh, well, we already shot it,

00:20:12.504 --> 00:20:15.215 position:50% align:center
so I guess there's no harm
if we put it up for 100 votes

00:20:15.298 --> 00:20:17.592 position:50% align:center
and just see what happens.

00:20:17.676 --> 00:20:21.262 position:50% align:center
[ROKO] I hope no one
I know in real life sees this.

00:20:24.516 --> 00:20:26.434 position:50% align:center
That love shout-out
was so sweet!

00:20:26.518 --> 00:20:29.187 position:50% align:center
It reminded me of my daughter
when she was a little girl!

00:20:29.270 --> 00:20:30.522 position:50% align:center
My grandson was crying,

00:20:30.605 --> 00:20:32.190 position:50% align:center
but as soon as he
watched your videos,

00:20:32.273 --> 00:20:33.400 position:50% align:center
it put him in a good mood.

00:20:33.483 --> 00:20:34.442 position:50% align:center
Thank you, ladies!

00:20:34.526 --> 00:20:36.361 position:50% align:center
Our grandpa is
probably watching it

00:20:36.444 --> 00:20:38.113 position:50% align:center
and smiling down from heaven!

00:20:38.196 --> 00:20:40.532 position:50% align:center
Thank you so much everyone--
you're too kind!

00:20:40.615 --> 00:20:43.034 position:50% align:center
So, it turns out there
was a demand, after all.

00:20:43.118 --> 00:20:45.954 position:50% align:center
I think it's cause
Miss Ino's so popular.

00:20:46.037 --> 00:20:48.039 position:50% align:center
It is still a
little embarrassing.

00:20:48.123 --> 00:20:50.041 position:50% align:center
Hayu, it seems like
your heartfelt video

00:20:50.125 --> 00:20:52.210 position:50% align:center
really cheered up all the
dads in the neighborhood!

00:20:52.293 --> 00:20:53.878 position:50% align:center
Whoa! You really think so?

00:20:53.962 --> 00:20:55.338 position:50% align:center
If we keep this up,

00:20:55.422 --> 00:20:57.841 position:50% align:center
I bet we could get even more
votes than Cream Anmitsu!

00:20:57.924 --> 00:21:00.468 position:50% align:center
I dunno--that seems
like kind of a long shot.

00:21:00.552 --> 00:21:01.553 position:50% align:center
It's about the intention

00:21:01.636 --> 00:21:03.471 position:50% align:center
and keeping up the
positive attitude!

00:21:03.555 --> 00:21:06.141 position:50% align:center
Okay, I guess that's true.

00:21:06.224 --> 00:21:08.101 position:50% align:center
All right, listen up, everyone!

00:21:08.184 --> 00:21:09.936 position:50% align:center
[GROUP grunts]

00:21:10.020 --> 00:21:12.355 position:50% align:center
Let's keep doing our best!

00:21:12.439 --> 00:21:14.941 position:50% align:center
[GROUP giggles]

00:21:15.025 --> 00:21:16.651 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Yeah!

00:21:18.778 --> 00:21:20.739 position:50% align:center
[TONE]
Sakura! Hayu!

00:21:20.822 --> 00:21:22.323 position:50% align:center
Hey, good morning!

00:21:22.407 --> 00:21:23.742 position:50% align:center
Nice to see you, Tone!

00:21:23.825 --> 00:21:25.535 position:50% align:center
How's it goin'?

00:21:25.618 --> 00:21:26.911 position:50% align:center
I stayed up three
nights in a row,

00:21:26.995 --> 00:21:29.581 position:50% align:center
but I finally maxed out
everyone's levels.

00:21:29.664 --> 00:21:31.958 position:50% align:center
[INO gasps] Please don't
lose sleep over the game!

00:21:32.042 --> 00:21:33.460 position:50% align:center
[TONE chuckles]

00:21:33.543 --> 00:21:35.003 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:21:35.086 --> 00:21:38.048 position:50% align:center
[INO] Why did Tone wrap all
those bandages around her phone?

00:21:38.131 --> 00:21:39.299 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:21:39.382 --> 00:21:42.093 position:50% align:center
[INO] Is it to prevent
her from spending money?

00:21:47.766 --> 00:21:49.059 position:50% align:center
[GROUP sighs]

00:21:49.142 --> 00:21:51.144 position:50% align:center
Even with Tone's and
our neighbors' help,

00:21:51.227 --> 00:21:53.104 position:50% align:center
it's still hard to compete
against these groups

00:21:53.188 --> 00:21:54.564 position:50% align:center
from all over the country.

00:21:54.647 --> 00:21:55.607 position:50% align:center
We need to come up with

00:21:55.690 --> 00:21:57.442 position:50% align:center
something else
to help us stand out.

00:21:57.525 --> 00:22:00.445 position:50% align:center
Maybe we can make a guest
appearance on another show.

00:22:00.528 --> 00:22:03.239 position:50% align:center
I know when a lot of
big comedians do TV shows,

00:22:03.323 --> 00:22:04.616 position:50% align:center
they like to have
idols on as guests,

00:22:04.699 --> 00:22:06.076 position:50% align:center
so they can tease them.

00:22:06.159 --> 00:22:08.244 position:50% align:center
Being featured on a music
show would be good, too!

00:22:08.328 --> 00:22:09.662 position:50% align:center
You're right!

00:22:09.746 --> 00:22:12.874 position:50% align:center
Or do you think it'd be possible
to appear on a TV drama?

00:22:12.957 --> 00:22:16.086 position:50% align:center
How about an anime theme
song with us as characters?

00:22:16.169 --> 00:22:17.253 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:22:17.337 --> 00:22:18.713 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Huh?

00:22:18.797 --> 00:22:20.423 position:50% align:center
Give me a break.

00:22:20.507 --> 00:22:22.258 position:50% align:center
If I had the industry
connections for all that,

00:22:22.342 --> 00:22:25.053 position:50% align:center
I wouldn't be in charge of
a bunch of second-rate idols.

00:22:25.136 --> 00:22:27.931 position:50% align:center
Jeez, why can't you at least
pretend to be encouraging?

00:22:28.014 --> 00:22:29.599 position:50% align:center
[HOHO] The company
doesn't have a big budget,

00:22:29.683 --> 00:22:31.059 position:50% align:center
so we just have to deal with it!

00:22:31.142 --> 00:22:32.894 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
That's not our fault!

00:22:33.895 --> 00:22:36.147 position:50% align:center
We may not have money,
but we still need a plan.

00:22:36.231 --> 00:22:38.441 position:50% align:center
C'mon, does anybody
have a suggestion?

00:22:38.525 --> 00:22:39.859 position:50% align:center
We need something cheap

00:22:39.943 --> 00:22:42.237 position:50% align:center
that lets us showcase our
talent and personalities.

00:22:42.320 --> 00:22:43.738 position:50% align:center
Personalities?

00:22:43.822 --> 00:22:45.407 position:50% align:center
I agree, we need to find a way

00:22:45.490 --> 00:22:47.742 position:50% align:center
to completely revamp
Fruit Tart's image.

00:22:47.826 --> 00:22:50.120 position:50% align:center
Revamp our image? I don't know.

00:22:52.789 --> 00:22:55.500 position:50% align:center
You okay? You look like you
might need to use the bathroom.

00:22:55.583 --> 00:22:57.752 position:50% align:center
I do not have to pee!

00:22:57.836 --> 00:23:00.922 position:50% align:center
Um, I think I have a suggestion.

00:23:01.006 --> 00:23:03.299 position:50% align:center
When Roko said we should
showcase ourselves,

00:23:03.383 --> 00:23:06.302 position:50% align:center
the first thing that came
to mind was this neighborhood.

00:23:06.386 --> 00:23:07.554 position:50% align:center
This neighborhood?

00:23:07.637 --> 00:23:11.182 position:50% align:center
Yes, this is our hometown.

00:23:11.266 --> 00:23:13.643 position:50% align:center
I think Fruit Tart should
put on a concert right here,

00:23:13.727 --> 00:23:15.520 position:50% align:center
at Higashi-Koganei!

00:23:15.603 --> 00:23:18.148 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
A concert at Higako?

00:23:20.358 --> 00:23:21.818 position:50% align:center
[HOHO]
Hmph!

